# ── EatNDeal: api + web local-only runtime data ─────────────────────
# Everything inside api/ and web/ except their source code stays on
# the developer's machine. User uploads, on-disk session/cache, secret
# credentials, OS junk — none of it belongs in git.
#
# Note: each folder also has its own nested .gitignore covering the
# same ground; these root-level entries are the single source of
# truth so the list is visible in one place.

# api — Node + Express + Knex
# (Git does NOT support trailing inline comments on patterns — a "# ..."
#  after the path becomes part of the pattern and stops it matching. Keep
#  every comment on its own line so the patterns below actually take.)
# customer-uploaded files (logos, banners, product photos)
api/uploads/
# any runtime cache / pid / lock files written by the api
api/runtime/
# rolled log output (if/when winston is wired)
api/logs/
# FCM push credentials — never commit
api/firebase-service-account.json
# secrets (db url, jwt secret, sms api key, oauth secrets)
api/.env

# web — Node + Express + EJS PWA
# on-disk session store (session-file-store), cache, etc.
web/runtime/
# rolled log output
web/logs/
# secrets (session secret, oauth client secrets, api url)
web/.env

# OS clutter that appears in both
api/.DS_Store
web/.DS_Store
api/Thumbs.db
web/Thumbs.db
ARCHITECTURE-REFERENCE.md
CODING-CONVENTIONS.md
EXISTING-CODEBASE.md
README.md
web/.env.example
api/.env.example
api/.env.example
web/public/service-worker.js

# Local-only seed / one-off scripts — never committed (they write demo
# data into the local DB). Keep them on the dev machine only.
api/scripts/seed-*.js
